CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1951, pg. 16 reads: "Pittsburgh's Pride - Members of Pittsburgh's bowling team who journeyed to Baltimore, Md., last week, are shown shortly before they departed. The event was the National Bowling Association Tourney held at the Strand Bowling Alleys, Friday, Saturday and Sunday.  The Pittsburgh team made a good showing in the competition with three of its members finishing in the money. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of the Pittsburgh bowling team, including Jasper Washington seated on suitcase, posed in front of Harmony Short Line bus before leaving for National Bowling Association Tourney in Baltimore
